WEBVTT

1
00:00:13.500 --> 00:00:16.236
Many people face the news each morning
每天早晨，很多人都面对着

2
00:00:16.260 --> 00:00:18.716
with trepidation and dread.
充满不安和恐惧的新闻。

3
00:00:18.740 --> 00:00:21.396
Every day, we read of shootings,
每天，我们都会读到枪击案，

4
00:00:21.420 --> 00:00:25.316
inequality, pollution, dictatorship,
不平等、污染、独裁统治、

5
00:00:25.340 --> 00:00:28.516
war and the spread of nuclear weapons.
战争和核武器扩散的消息。

6
00:00:28.540 --> 00:00:30.276
These are some of the reasons
这些是 2016 年

7
00:00:30.300 --> 00:00:35.756
that 2016 was called the "Worst. Year. Ever."
被称为“史上最糟糕的一年”的部分原因。

8
00:00:35.780 --> 00:00:38.356
Until 2017 claimed that record --
直到 2017 年再创新高——

9
00:00:38.380 --> 00:00:39.436
(Laughter)
（笑声）

10
00:00:39.460 --> 00:00:42.036
and left many people longing for earlier decades,
这使得很多人不禁 怀念几十年前的日子，

11
00:00:42.060 --> 00:00:45.380
when the world seemed safer, cleaner and more equal.
那时世界看来更安全，清净和平等。

12
00:00:46.380 --> 00:00:49.956
But is this a sensible way to understand the human condition
但这是理解 21 世纪人类生存状况的

13
00:00:49.980 --> 00:00:51.956
in the 21st century?
合理方式吗？

14
00:00:51.980 --> 00:00:54.756
As Franklin Pierce Adams pointed out,
就如富兰克林 · 皮尔斯 · 亚当斯指出的那样：

15
00:00:54.780 --> 00:00:57.476
"Nothing is more responsible for the good old days
“怀念往昔美好时光的人的记忆

16
00:00:57.500 --> 00:00:58.716
than a bad memory."
一定糟透了。“

17
00:00:58.740 --> 00:01:01.476
(Laughter)
（笑声）

18
00:01:01.500 --> 00:01:04.876
You can always fool yourself into seeing a decline
如果你拿现在的新闻头条

19
00:01:04.900 --> 00:01:07.596
if you compare bleeding headlines of the present
跟过去玫瑰色的图片相对比，

20
00:01:07.620 --> 00:01:10.716
with rose-tinted images of the past.
你就总会以为自己 正面临着世风日下的局面。

21
00:01:10.740 --> 00:01:13.156
What does the trajectory of the world look like
当我们用恒定的尺度 来衡量幸福感时，

22
00:01:13.180 --> 00:01:17.436
when we measure well-being over time using a constant yardstick?
世界的变化轨迹会是什么样呢？

23
00:01:17.460 --> 00:01:20.156
Let's compare the most recent data on the present
让我们用同样的方法 来比较最新的数据

24
00:01:20.180 --> 00:01:22.180
with the same measures 30 years ago.
和 30 年前的数据。

25
00:01:23.140 --> 00:01:28.276
Last year, Americans killed each other at a rate of 5.3 per hundred thousand,
去年，美国每 10 万人中有  5.3 人死于凶杀，

26
00:01:28.300 --> 00:01:31.676
had seven percent of their citizens in poverty
7%的贫困人口，

27
00:01:31.700 --> 00:01:34.956
and emitted 21 million tons of particulate matter
排放了 2100 万吨的微粒物质，

28
00:01:34.980 --> 00:01:38.076
and four million tons of sulfur dioxide.
以及 400 万吨的二氧化硫。

29
00:01:38.100 --> 00:01:42.236
But 30 years ago, the homicide rate was 8.5 per hundred thousand,
而 30 年前，每 10 万人中 有 8.5 人死于凶杀，

30
00:01:42.260 --> 00:01:44.356
poverty rate was 12 percent
贫困率为 12 %，

31
00:01:44.380 --> 00:01:47.556
and we emitted 35 million tons of particulate matter
我们排放了 3500 万吨的微粒物质，

32
00:01:47.580 --> 00:01:50.300
and 20 million tons of sulfur dioxide.
以及 2000 万吨的二氧化硫。

33
00:01:51.220 --> 00:01:53.276
What about the world as a whole?
那么世界整体情况如何？

34
00:01:53.300 --> 00:01:56.716
Last year, the world had 12 ongoing wars,
去年，全球共有 12 场战争，

35
00:01:56.740 --> 00:01:58.876
60 autocracies,
60 个独裁政权，

36
00:01:58.900 --> 00:02:02.516
10 percent of the world population in extreme poverty
10% 的极端贫穷人口

37
00:02:02.540 --> 00:02:05.516
and more than 10,000 nuclear weapons.
以及超过 1 万件核武器。

38
00:02:05.540 --> 00:02:08.036
But 30 years ago, there were 23 wars,
而 30 年前，一共有 23 场战争，

39
00:02:08.060 --> 00:02:09.956
85 autocracies,
85 个独裁政权，

40
00:02:09.980 --> 00:02:13.596
37 percent of the world population in extreme poverty
37 %的全球人口极度贫困

41
00:02:13.620 --> 00:02:16.420
and more than 60,000 nuclear weapons.
以及超过 6 万件核武器。

42
00:02:17.020 --> 00:02:21.555
True, last year was a terrible year for terrorism in Western Europe,
的确，去年是西欧恐怖主义 十分猖獗的一年，

43
00:02:21.579 --> 00:02:23.796
with 238 deaths,
共造成 238 人死亡，

44
00:02:23.820 --> 00:02:27.020
but 1988 was worse with 440 deaths.
但 1988 年更糟，有 440 人死亡。

45
00:02:28.260 --> 00:02:29.796
What's going on?
这是怎么回事？

46
00:02:29.820 --> 00:02:33.316
Was 1988 a particularly bad year?
1988 年是尤其糟糕的一年吗？

47
00:02:33.340 --> 00:02:37.396
Or are these improvements a sign that the world, for all its struggles,
或者，这是世界进步的迹象，

48
00:02:37.420 --> 00:02:39.060
gets better over time?
在挣扎中，越变越好？

49
00:02:39.620 --> 00:02:44.420
Might we even invoke the admittedly old-fashioned notion of progress?
我们是否可以援引 公认的过时了进步观念？

50
00:02:45.700 --> 00:02:48.996
To do so is to court a certain amount of derision,
这样做会招来一些嘲笑，

51
00:02:49.020 --> 00:02:52.796
because I have found that intellectuals hate progress.
因为我发现知识分子憎恨进步。

52
00:02:52.820 --> 00:02:54.636
(Laughter)
（笑声）

53
00:02:54.660 --> 00:02:57.476
(Applause)
（鼓掌）

54
00:02:57.500 --> 00:03:01.196
And intellectuals who call themselves progressive really hate progress.
自称进步的知识分子真的讨厌进步。

55
00:03:01.220 --> 00:03:02.356
(Laughter)
（笑声）

56
00:03:02.380 --> 00:03:05.716
Now, it's not that they hate the fruits of progress, mind you.
请注意，我并不是说 他们讨厌进步的成果。

57
00:03:05.740 --> 00:03:08.356
Most academics and pundits
大多数学者和专家

58
00:03:08.380 --> 00:03:11.820
would rather have their surgery with anesthesia than without it.
做手术时还是会选择用麻醉， 而非什么都不用。

59
00:03:12.900 --> 00:03:17.156
It's the idea of progress that rankles the chattering class.
让这些喋喋不休的人不满的， 是进步的观点。

60
00:03:17.180 --> 00:03:20.916
If you believe that humans can improve their lot, I have been told,
如果你相信人类可以改善命运， 正如我被告知的那样，

61
00:03:20.940 --> 00:03:23.316
that means that you have a blind faith
这意味着你有着盲目的信仰，

62
00:03:23.340 --> 00:03:27.916
and a quasi-religious belief in the outmoded superstition
一种类似宗教的落后迷信，

63
00:03:25.736 --> 00:03:31.786
and the false promise of the myth of the onward march
相信对不可阻挡的进步神话的

64
00:03:31.780 --> 00:03:33.820
of inexorable progress.
虚假承诺。

65
00:03:34.460 --> 00:03:38.796
You are a cheerleader for vulgar American can-doism,
你是粗俗的美国佬的啦啦队长，

66
00:03:38.820 --> 00:03:42.036
with the rah-rah spirit of boardroom ideology,
拥有董事会的意识形态，硅谷和商会的

67
00:03:42.060 --> 00:03:45.116
Silicon Valley and the Chamber of Commerce.
拉拉队精神。

68
00:03:45.140 --> 00:03:47.996
You are a practitioner of Whig history,
你是辉格历史的实践者，

69
00:03:48.020 --> 00:03:52.156
a naive optimist, a Pollyanna and, of course, a Pangloss,
一位天真的乐观主义者， 你就像是潘格劳斯，

70
00:03:52.180 --> 00:03:54.836
alluding to the Voltaire character who declared,
伏尔泰小说里的角色，曾宣称：

71
00:03:54.860 --> 00:03:58.196
"All is for the best in the best of all possible worlds."
“在理想的最美好的世界中， 一切都是为最美好的目的而设。“

72
00:03:58.220 --> 00:04:01.716
Well, Professor Pangloss, as it happens, was a pessimist.
好吧，潘格劳斯教授 碰巧是个悲观主义者。

73
00:04:01.740 --> 00:04:04.396
A true optimist believes there can be much better worlds
一个真正的乐观主义者相信 存在着比我们今天拥有的

74
00:04:04.420 --> 00:04:05.956
than the one we have today.
更好的世界。

75
00:04:05.980 --> 00:04:07.636
But all of this is irrelevant,
但所有这些都无关紧要，

76
00:04:07.660 --> 00:04:10.436
because the question of whether progress has taken place
因为进步是否发生

77
00:04:10.460 --> 00:04:12.196
is not a matter of faith
与信念无关，

78
00:04:12.220 --> 00:04:16.036
or having an optimistic temperament or seeing the glass as half full.
也不取决于是否拥有乐观气质， 或是看到了半杯水（而不是半个空杯子）。

79
00:04:16.060 --> 00:04:17.900
It's a testable hypothesis.
而是一个可检验的假设。

80
00:04:18.540 --> 00:04:19.916
For all their differences,
尽管各有分歧，

81
00:04:19.940 --> 00:04:24.316
people largely agree on what goes into human well-being:
在很大程度上人们会一致认为， 人类的幸福包括以下因素：

82
00:04:24.340 --> 00:04:30.036
life, health, sustenance, prosperity, peace, freedom, safety, knowledge,
生命、健康、生计、繁荣、 和平、自由、安全、知识、

83
00:04:30.060 --> 00:04:32.036
leisure, happiness.
休闲、快乐。

84
00:04:32.060 --> 00:04:33.956
All of these things can be measured.
这些东西都可以测量。

85
00:04:33.980 --> 00:04:38.316
If they have improved over time, that, I submit, is progress.
如果它们随时间得到改善， 我认为就是进步。

86
00:04:38.340 --> 00:04:39.956
Let's go to the data,
让我们看看数据。

87
00:04:39.980 --> 00:04:43.596
beginning with the most precious thing of all, life.
从最珍贵的东西开始，生命。

88
00:04:43.620 --> 00:04:48.196
For most of human history, life expectancy at birth was around 30.
在人类历史长河的大部分时期中， 预期寿命为 30 岁上下。

89
00:04:48.220 --> 00:04:50.996
Today, worldwide, it is more than 70,
今天，全球平均寿命超过了70岁，

90
00:04:51.020 --> 00:04:52.956
and in the developed parts of the world,
在发达国家，

91
00:04:52.980 --> 00:04:54.180
more than 80.
则超过80岁。

92
00:04:54.860 --> 00:04:57.996
250 years ago, in the richest countries of the world,
250 年前，在全球最富有的国家，

93
00:04:58.020 --> 00:05:02.036
a third of the children did not live to see their fifth birthday,
在风险被降低一百倍之前，

94
00:05:02.060 --> 00:05:05.396
before the risk was brought down a hundredfold.
1/3 的儿童活不到五岁。

95
00:05:05.420 --> 00:05:08.676
Today, that fate befalls less than six percent of children
今天，婴儿死亡率在全球最贫穷的国家

96
00:05:08.700 --> 00:05:10.540
in the poorest countries of the world.
也已经降低到 6 %以下。

97
00:05:11.420 --> 00:05:14.836
Famine is one of the Four Horsemen of the Apocalypse.
饥荒是世界末日的四骑士之一。

98
00:05:14.860 --> 00:05:18.116
It could bring devastation to any part of the world.
它可以给世界上任何地方带来毁灭。

99
00:05:18.140 --> 00:05:20.076
Today, famine has been banished
今天，饥荒已经被驱逐至

100
00:05:20.100 --> 00:05:22.700
to the most remote and war-ravaged regions.
最偏远和饱受战争蹂躏的地区。

101
00:05:23.500 --> 00:05:26.636
200 years ago, 90 percent of the world's population
200 年前，90 %的世界人口

102
00:05:26.660 --> 00:05:28.836
subsisted in extreme poverty.
处于极端贫困。

103
00:05:28.860 --> 00:05:31.420
Today, fewer than 10 percent of people do.
今天只有不到 10 %的人如此。

104
00:05:32.540 --> 00:05:34.036
For most of human history,
在人类大部分的历史中，

105
00:05:34.060 --> 00:05:36.116
the powerful states and empires
强大的国家和帝国

106
00:05:36.140 --> 00:05:38.756
were pretty much always at war with each other,
总是彼此交战，

107
00:05:38.780 --> 00:05:42.236
and peace was a mere interlude between wars.
而和平只是战争之间的插曲。

108
00:05:42.260 --> 00:05:44.516
Today, they are never at war with each other.
今天，他们不再彼此开战。

109
00:05:44.540 --> 00:05:45.836
The last great power war
上一场大国之间的战争

110
00:05:45.860 --> 00:05:48.980
pitted the United States against China 65 years ago.
发生在 65 年前的中国和美国。

111
00:05:49.980 --> 00:05:54.716
More recently, wars of all kinds have become fewer and less deadly.
最近，各种各样的战争发生得 越来越少，伤亡人数也有所下降。

112
00:05:54.740 --> 00:05:59.196
The annual rate of war has fallen from about 22 per hundred thousand per year
每年的战争死亡率 从 50 年代的 10 万分之 22

113
00:05:59.220 --> 00:06:02.836
in the early '50s to 1.2 today.
下降至今天的 10 万分之 1.2。

114
00:06:02.860 --> 00:06:05.436
Democracy has suffered obvious setbacks
民主在委内瑞拉，俄罗斯，土耳其

115
00:06:05.460 --> 00:06:09.076
in Venezuela, in Russia, in Turkey
遭受了明显的挫折，

116
00:06:09.100 --> 00:06:12.196
and is threatened by the rise of authoritarian populism
并在东欧和美国受到了

117
00:06:12.220 --> 00:06:14.836
in Eastern Europe and the United States.
来自独裁民粹主义崛起的威胁。

118
00:06:14.860 --> 00:06:17.556
Yet the world has never been more democratic
但是相比过去的时代，

119
00:06:17.580 --> 00:06:19.556
than it has been in the past decade,
世界从来没有如此民主，

120
00:06:19.580 --> 00:06:22.780
with two-thirds of the world's people living in democracies.
全球 2/3 的人口生活在民主国家。

121
00:06:24.100 --> 00:06:28.236
Homicide rates plunge whenever anarchy and the code of vendetta
每当无政府状态和仇杀行为 被法治取代时，

122
00:06:28.260 --> 00:06:30.636
are replaced by the rule of law.
凶杀犯罪率就会下降。

123
00:06:30.660 --> 00:06:34.876
It happened when feudal Europe was brought under the control of centralized kingdoms,
这发生在封建的欧洲 被中央王国控制时，

124
00:06:34.900 --> 00:06:37.036
so that today a Western European
所以今天西欧人

125
00:06:37.060 --> 00:06:39.636
has 1/35th the chance of being murdered
被谋杀的几率是

126
00:06:39.660 --> 00:06:42.236
compared to his medieval ancestors.
他们中世纪祖先的 1/35。

127
00:06:42.260 --> 00:06:44.716
It happened again in colonial New England,
这也发生在新英格兰的殖民地，

128
00:06:44.740 --> 00:06:48.276
in the American Wild West when the sheriffs moved to town,
治安官进驻后的美国西部小镇，

129
00:06:48.300 --> 00:06:49.996
and in Mexico.
以及墨西哥等地。

130
00:06:50.020 --> 00:06:53.540
Indeed, we've become safer in just about every way.
我们的确在各个方面 都变得更安全了。

131
00:06:54.380 --> 00:06:57.916
Over the last century, we've become 96 percent less likely
上个世纪以来， 我们死于交通事故的概率

132
00:06:57.940 --> 00:07:00.196
to be killed in a car crash,
降低了 96 %。

133
00:07:00.220 --> 00:07:04.156
88 percent less likely to be mowed down on the sidewalk,
在人行道上被撞倒的概率 降低了88 %。

134
00:07:04.180 --> 00:07:07.916
99 percent less likely to die in a plane crash,
飞机事故死亡率下降了 99 %。

135
00:07:07.940 --> 00:07:11.596
95 percent less likely to be killed on the job,
因公殉职的概率也降低了 95 %。

136
00:07:11.620 --> 00:07:15.236
89 percent less likely to be killed by an act of God,
死于大自然因素的 概率也降低了 89 %，

137
00:07:15.260 --> 00:07:19.196
such as a drought, flood, wildfire, storm, volcano,
比如干旱，洪水，野火，风暴，火山，

138
00:07:19.220 --> 00:07:21.876
landslide, earthquake or meteor strike,
山崩、地震或流星撞击。

139
00:07:21.900 --> 00:07:25.156
presumably not because God has become less angry with us
应该不是因为 上帝对我们不再那么生气了，

140
00:07:25.180 --> 00:07:29.916
but because of improvements in the resilience of our infrastructure.
而是因为我们的基础设施的 应变能力提高了。

141
00:07:29.940 --> 00:07:33.196
And what about the quintessential act of God,
那么，典型的天灾，

142
00:07:33.220 --> 00:07:36.716
the projectile hurled by Zeus himself?
宙斯自己投掷的炮弹呢？

143
00:07:36.740 --> 00:07:40.980
Yes, we are 97 percent less likely to be killed by a bolt of lightning.
没错，我们被闪电击中的 概率降低了 97 %。

144
00:07:43.300 --> 00:07:44.956
Before the 17th century,
17 世纪以前，

145
00:07:44.980 --> 00:07:48.516
no more than 15 percent of Europeans could read or write.
不到 15 %的欧洲人能读会写。

146
00:07:48.540 --> 00:07:51.676
Europe and the United States achieved universal literacy
欧洲和美国在 20 世纪中叶

147
00:07:51.700 --> 00:07:53.636
by the middle of the 20th century,
就消灭了文盲，

148
00:07:53.660 --> 00:07:56.156
and the rest of the world is catching up.
世界其他地方也在陆续跟上。

149
00:07:56.180 --> 00:07:59.596
Today, more than 90 percent of the world's population
今天，全球年龄在 25 岁以下的人中，

150
00:07:59.620 --> 00:08:02.060
under the age of 25 can read and write.
超过 90 %的人口能读会写。

151
00:08:03.260 --> 00:08:07.236
In the 19th century, Westerners worked more than 60 hours per week.
在 19 世纪，西方人每周工作时间 远远超过 60 个小时。

152
00:08:07.260 --> 00:08:09.180
Today, they work fewer than 40.
今天，这个数字已经低于 40 小时。

153
00:08:10.260 --> 00:08:14.676
Thanks to the universal penetration of running water and electricity
得益于发达国家

154
00:08:12.676 --> 00:08:16.096
in the developed world
自来水和电的普及，

155
00:08:16.100 --> 00:08:20.076
and the widespread adoption of washing machines, vacuum cleaners,
以及洗衣机，真空吸尘器，

156
00:08:20.100 --> 00:08:24.076
refrigerators, dishwashers, stoves and microwaves,
冰箱、洗碗机、炉子和 微波炉的广泛使用，

157
00:08:24.100 --> 00:08:26.996
the amount of our lives that we forfeit to housework
我们花费在家务上的时间

158
00:08:27.020 --> 00:08:29.396
has fallen from 60 hours a week
从一周 60 个小时

159
00:08:29.420 --> 00:08:31.380
to fewer than 15 hours a week.
下降至每周不到 15 小时。

160
00:08:32.580 --> 00:08:37.116
Do all of these gains in health, wealth, safety, knowledge and leisure
在健康、财富、安全、知识 和休闲方面的这些进步

161
00:08:37.140 --> 00:08:38.836
make us any happier?
让我们更加幸福了吗？

162
00:08:38.860 --> 00:08:40.076
The answer is yes.
答案是肯定的。

163
00:08:40.100 --> 00:08:42.276
In 86 percent of the world's countries,
全球 86 %的国家中，

164
00:08:42.300 --> 00:08:44.660
happiness has increased in recent decades.
幸福指数在最近几十年来都在增长。

165
00:08:45.619 --> 00:08:47.355
Well, I hope to have convinced you
好了，我希望我已经说服你们

166
00:08:47.379 --> 00:08:50.796
that progress is not a matter of faith or optimism,
进步无关信念或乐观，

167
00:08:50.820 --> 00:08:52.955
but is a fact of human history,
而是人类历史的事实，

168
00:08:52.979 --> 00:08:55.540
indeed the greatest fact in human history.
确实是人类历史上最伟大的事实。

169
00:08:56.300 --> 00:08:59.116
And how has this fact been covered in the news?
而这些事实是如何 被新闻媒体报道的呢？

170
00:08:59.140 --> 00:09:02.300
(Laughter)
（笑声）

171
00:09:03.180 --> 00:09:07.156
A tabulation of positive and negative emotion words in news stories
新闻故事中积极和消极的情绪词汇表

172
00:09:07.180 --> 00:09:10.836
has shown that during the decades in which humanity has gotten healthier,
已证明，在过去几十年里 人类变得更健康，

173
00:09:10.860 --> 00:09:13.676
wealthier, wiser, safer and happier,
更富有，更聪明，更安全，更快乐。

174
00:09:13.700 --> 00:09:17.796
the "New York Times" has become increasingly morose
《纽约时报》的措辞却变得越来越阴郁，

175
00:09:17.820 --> 00:09:21.420
and the world's broadcasts too have gotten steadily glummer.
全球的广播节目的腔调 也变得越来越阴沉。

176
00:09:22.540 --> 00:09:25.236
Why don't people appreciate progress?
为什么人们不感激这些进步？

177
00:09:25.260 --> 00:09:28.236
Part of the answer comes from our cognitive psychology.
部分答案来自于我们的认知心理学。

178
00:09:28.260 --> 00:09:33.276
We estimate risk using a mental shortcut called the "availability heuristic."
我们用一个名为“可得性启发”的 心理捷径来估计危险。

179
00:09:33.300 --> 00:09:36.076
The easier it is to recall something from memory,
一件越容易被回忆起来的事，

180
00:09:36.100 --> 00:09:38.100
the more probable we judge it to be.
我们就越可能认为它就是那样。

181
00:09:39.020 --> 00:09:42.636
The other part of the answer comes from the nature of journalism,
另外一部分答案来自于新闻业的本质，

182
00:09:42.660 --> 00:09:46.036
captured in this satirical headline from "The Onion,"
这个讽刺性的头条取自“洋葱新闻“，

183
00:09:46.060 --> 00:09:48.116
"CNN Holds Morning Meeting to Decide
“美国有线电视新闻网 CNN 开早会决定

184
00:09:48.140 --> 00:09:50.436
What Viewers Should Panic About For Rest of Day."
观众在这一天应当对什么感到恐慌。“

185
00:09:50.460 --> 00:09:52.156
(Laughter)
（笑声）

186
00:09:52.180 --> 00:09:56.220
(Applause)
（掌声）

187
00:09:56.980 --> 00:10:00.796
News is about stuff that happens, not stuff that doesn't happen.
新闻是报道那些正在发生的事， 而不是没有发生的事。

188
00:10:00.820 --> 00:10:03.196
You never see a journalist who says,
你从没见过一个记者说，

189
00:10:03.220 --> 00:10:07.436
"I'm reporting live from a country that has been at peace for 40 years,"
“我正在一个40年来 局势都很稳定的国家直播”，

190
00:10:07.460 --> 00:10:10.100
or a city that has not been attacked by terrorists.
或者在一个从来没有被 恐怖分子袭击的城市直播。

191
00:10:10.780 --> 00:10:13.116
Also, bad things can happen quickly,
另外，坏事可能会瞬间发生，

192
00:10:13.140 --> 00:10:15.556
but good things aren't built in a day.
但是好事却不是一天能成的。

193
00:10:15.580 --> 00:10:17.476
The papers could have run the headline,
新闻媒体可以在 过去25年中。每天都使用

194
00:10:17.500 --> 00:10:21.876
"137,000 people escaped from extreme poverty yesterday"
“昨天有 13 万 7 千人脱离了极端贫困”

195
00:10:21.900 --> 00:10:24.756
every day for the last 25 years.
这个标题。

196
00:10:24.780 --> 00:10:28.996
That's one and a quarter billion people leaving poverty behind,
也就是说，总共有 12.5 亿人脱离了贫困，

197
00:10:29.020 --> 00:10:31.036
but you never read about it.
但是你从来没有看到过这一条新闻。

198
00:10:31.060 --> 00:10:34.356
Also, the news capitalizes on our morbid interest
而且，新闻报道还会利用我们对

199
00:10:32.946 --> 00:10:35.666
in what can go wrong,
哪里会出现问题的病态兴趣，

200
00:10:35.660 --> 00:10:39.996
captured in the programming policy, "If it bleeds, it leads."
其规划政策是“越血腥越吸睛”。

201
00:10:40.020 --> 00:10:43.756
Well, if you combine our cognitive biases with the nature of news,
如果将我们的认知偏差和 新闻的本质相结合，

202
00:10:43.780 --> 00:10:46.476
you can see why the world has been coming to an end
你就可以了解为什么这个世界

203
00:10:46.500 --> 00:10:48.460
for a very long time indeed.
的确是在很久以前 就开始走向末日了。

204
00:10:50.660 --> 00:10:52.756
Let me address some questions about progress
让我提出几个关于进步的问题，

205
00:10:52.780 --> 00:10:55.140
that no doubt have occurred to many of you.
豪无疑问这些进步 在你们很多人身上都发生过。

206
00:10:56.140 --> 00:10:58.876
First, isn't it good to be pessimistic
首先，成为一个悲观主义者，

207
00:10:58.900 --> 00:11:01.316
to safeguard against complacency,
可以防范自满、清清除糟粕，

208
00:11:01.340 --> 00:11:03.996
to rake the muck, to speak truth to power?
向当权者说实话，这有什么不好吗？

209
00:11:04.020 --> 00:11:05.996
Well, not exactly.
其实，这样未必好。

210
00:11:06.020 --> 00:11:07.996
It's good to be accurate.
能做到精确是很好的。

211
00:11:08.020 --> 00:11:10.476
Of course we should be aware of suffering and danger
当然我们都应当知道

212
00:11:09.596 --> 00:11:11.956
wherever they occur,
痛苦和危险发生的地方，

213
00:11:11.940 --> 00:11:14.956
but we should also be aware of how they can be reduced,
但是我们也应当知道 如何去减少它们。

214
00:11:14.980 --> 00:11:18.476
because there are dangers to indiscriminate pessimism.
因为不分青红皂白的 悲观主义是危险的。

215
00:11:18.500 --> 00:11:20.156
One of them is fatalism.
其中一个例子就是宿命论。

216
00:11:20.180 --> 00:11:22.356
If all our efforts at improving the world
如果我们所有 推动这个世界进步的努力

217
00:11:22.380 --> 00:11:23.676
have been in vain,
都是徒劳的，

218
00:11:23.700 --> 00:11:25.556
why throw good money after bad?
为什么我们还要去做无用功？

219
00:11:25.580 --> 00:11:27.152
The poor will always be with you.
反正贫穷无论如何都会一直跟随你。

220
00:11:28.100 --> 00:11:30.396
And since the world will end soon --
并且既然这个世界 很快就要完蛋了——

221
00:11:30.420 --> 00:11:32.276
if climate change doesn't kill us all,
如果气候变化没有将我们全都干掉，

222
00:11:32.300 --> 00:11:34.756
then runaway artificial intelligence will --
那么失控的人工智能也会——

223
00:11:34.780 --> 00:11:38.396
a natural response is to enjoy life while we can,
自然的反应就是，乐在当下吧，

224
00:11:38.420 --> 00:11:41.180
eat, drink and be merry, for tomorrow we die.
吃喝玩乐，同时坐以待毙。

225
00:11:42.660 --> 00:11:45.956
The other danger of thoughtless pessimism is radicalism.
轻率的悲观主义的 另一个危险是激进主义。

226
00:11:45.980 --> 00:11:49.996
If our institutions are all failing and beyond hope for reform,
如果我们的机构都失败了， 改革的希望也破灭了，

227
00:11:50.020 --> 00:11:53.676
a natural response is to seek to smash the machine,
自然的反应就是砸烂机器，

228
00:11:53.700 --> 00:11:54.916
drain the swamp,
抽干沼泽，

229
00:11:54.940 --> 00:11:56.716
burn the empire to the ground,
把帝国烧成灰烬，

230
00:11:56.740 --> 00:12:00.036
on the hope that whatever rises out of the ashes
抱着灰烬中无论长出什么

231
00:12:00.060 --> 00:12:02.300
is bound to be better than what we have now.
都要好于当下的幻想。

232
00:12:03.740 --> 00:12:05.796
Well, if there is such a thing as progress,
那么，如果真的有进步这个东西，

233
00:12:05.820 --> 00:12:07.076
what causes it?
是什么导致了进步呢？

234
00:12:07.100 --> 00:12:12.276
Progress is not some mystical force or dialectic lifting us ever higher.
进步并不是某种神秘力量或辩证法， 可以将我们推向更高的境界。

235
00:12:12.300 --> 00:12:15.876
It's not a mysterious arc of history bending toward justice.
它不是一条屈服于正义的神秘弧线。

236
00:12:15.900 --> 00:12:19.636
It's the result of human efforts governed by an idea,
进步是人类在一种思想 指引下努力的结果。

237
00:12:19.660 --> 00:12:23.676
an idea that we associate with the 18th century Enlightenment,
这个思想与 18 世纪的启蒙运动有关，

238
00:12:23.700 --> 00:12:28.036
namely that if we apply reason and science
那就是，如果我们运用理性和科学

239
00:12:28.060 --> 00:12:30.116
that enhance human well-being,
来提高人类的幸福水平，

240
00:12:30.140 --> 00:12:31.780
we can gradually succeed.
我们就可以逐渐取得成功。

241
00:12:32.500 --> 00:12:35.956
Is progress inevitable? Of course not.
进步是不可避免的吗? 当然不是。

242
00:12:35.980 --> 00:12:38.996
Progress does not mean that everything becomes better
进步并不意味着所有人在任何地方，

243
00:12:38.246 --> 00:12:41.986
for everyone everywhere all the time.
任何时候都能变得更好。

244
00:12:41.980 --> 00:12:45.236
That would be a miracle, and progress is not a miracle
那就算得上是一个奇迹， 但进步并不是奇迹，

245
00:12:45.260 --> 00:12:46.460
but problem-solving.
而是解决问题的过程。

246
00:12:47.180 --> 00:12:49.036
Problems are inevitable
问题不可避免，

247
00:12:49.060 --> 00:12:52.740
and solutions create new problems which have to be solved in their turn.
解决问题的方案还会带来新的问题， 这些问题在未来必须解决。

248
00:12:53.580 --> 00:12:57.276
The unsolved problems facing the world today are gargantuan,
当今世界面临的 未解决的问题是巨大的，

249
00:12:57.300 --> 00:13:00.076
including the risks of climate change
包括气候变化

250
00:13:00.100 --> 00:13:01.716
and nuclear war,
和核武战争的风险。

251
00:13:01.740 --> 00:13:04.276
but we must see them as problems to be solved,
我们必须将其视为需要解决的问题，

252
00:13:04.300 --> 00:13:06.716
not apocalypses in waiting,
不能坐以待毙，

253
00:13:06.740 --> 00:13:08.996
and aggressively pursue solutions
而要积极寻求解决之道，

254
00:13:09.020 --> 00:13:11.876
like Deep Decarbonization for climate change
比如以深脱碳技术对应气候变化，

255
00:13:11.900 --> 00:13:14.100
and Global Zero for nuclear war.
和全球零核战。

256
00:13:15.580 --> 00:13:19.476
Finally, does the Enlightenment go against human nature?
最后一点，启蒙运动 是否违背了人类的本性？

257
00:13:19.500 --> 00:13:21.796
This is an acute question for me,
这对我来说是个尖锐的问题，

258
00:13:21.820 --> 00:13:25.236
because I'm a prominent advocate of the existence of human nature,
因为我是人类本性天然存在 这一观点的主要倡导者，

259
00:13:25.260 --> 00:13:28.676
with all its shortcomings and perversities.
尽管其中存在许多的缺点和不足。

260
00:13:28.700 --> 00:13:30.116
In my book "The Blank Slate,"
在我的书《白板》中，

261
00:13:30.140 --> 00:13:34.276
I argued that the human prospect is more tragic than utopian
我认为人类的前景比乌托邦更悲惨，

262
00:13:34.300 --> 00:13:37.036
and that we are not stardust, we are not golden
我们不是星尘，我们不是金色的，

263
00:13:37.060 --> 00:13:39.596
and there's no way we are getting back to the garden.
我们不可能回到伊甸园。

264
00:13:39.620 --> 00:13:42.116
(Laughter)
（笑声）

265
00:13:42.140 --> 00:13:44.436
But my worldview has lightened up
但是我的世界观

266
00:13:44.460 --> 00:13:47.396
in the 15 years since "The Blank Slate" was published.
随着 15 年前《白板》的出版改变了。

267
00:13:47.420 --> 00:13:50.356
My acquaintance with the statistics of human progress,
我对人类进步的统计数据的接触——

268
00:13:50.380 --> 00:13:51.716
starting with violence
从暴力开始，

269
00:13:51.740 --> 00:13:55.516
but now encompassing every other aspect of our well-being,
到现在涵盖了我们幸福的每一个方面——

270
00:13:55.540 --> 00:13:57.116
has fortified my belief
强化了我的信念，

271
00:13:57.140 --> 00:14:00.316
that in understanding our tribulations and woes,
即我们的困难和困境，

272
00:14:00.340 --> 00:14:02.116
human nature is the problem,
人性是主要的问题，

273
00:14:02.140 --> 00:14:06.476
but human nature, channeled by Enlightenment norms and institutions,
但是人性，在启蒙运动的 规范和制度引导下，

274
00:14:06.500 --> 00:14:07.700
is also the solution.
也可以是解决方案。

275
00:14:09.020 --> 00:14:13.916
Admittedly, it's not easy to replicate my own data-driven epiphany
不可否认，让人类普遍复制 我通过数据得到的洞察

276
00:14:13.940 --> 00:14:16.276
with humanity at large.
并不容易。

277
00:14:16.300 --> 00:14:18.116
Some intellectuals have responded
有些学者愤怒地反击

278
00:14:18.140 --> 00:14:20.836
with fury to my book "Enlightenment Now,"
我的书《当下的启蒙》说：

279
00:14:20.860 --> 00:14:25.116
saying first how dare he claim that intellectuals hate progress,
首先，他怎么敢宣称 知识分子痛恨进步，

280
00:14:25.140 --> 00:14:28.276
and second, how dare he claim that there has been progress.
第二，他怎么敢宣称 世界已经取得了进步。

281
00:14:28.300 --> 00:14:30.980
(Laughter)
（笑声）

282
00:14:32.060 --> 00:14:35.676
With others, the idea of progress just leaves them cold.
和其他人一样， 进步的概念对他们毫无意义。

283
00:14:35.700 --> 00:14:37.396
Saving the lives of billions,
拯救数十亿人的生命，

284
00:14:37.420 --> 00:14:40.316
eradicating disease, feeding the hungry,
消灭疾病，养活饥民，

285
00:14:40.340 --> 00:14:41.780
teaching kids to read?
教孩子识字？

286
00:14:42.380 --> 00:14:43.580
Boring.
太无聊了。

287
00:14:44.540 --> 00:14:49.036
At the same time, the most common response I have received from readers is gratitude,
同时，我得到的最常见的 反馈是读者的感谢，

288
00:14:49.060 --> 00:14:51.436
gratitude for changing their view of the world
为改变了他们对世界的看法而感激，

289
00:14:51.460 --> 00:14:53.996
from a numb and helpless fatalism
从麻木和无助的宿命论

290
00:14:54.020 --> 00:14:55.676
to something more constructive,
变得更具建设性，

291
00:14:55.700 --> 00:14:57.436
even heroic.
甚至更英勇。

292
00:14:57.460 --> 00:14:59.636
I believe that the ideals of the Enlightenment
我相信启蒙运动的理想

293
00:14:59.660 --> 00:15:01.676
can be cast a stirring narrative,
可以是一种激动人心的叙述。

294
00:15:01.700 --> 00:15:04.516
and I hope that people with greater artistic flare
我希望那些比我拥有 更丰富的艺术灵感

295
00:15:04.540 --> 00:15:06.556
and rhetorical power than I
和修辞力量的人，

296
00:15:06.580 --> 00:15:09.596
can tell it better and spread it further.
能够把这个故事讲述得更好， 并传播得更远。

297
00:15:09.620 --> 00:15:11.060
It goes something like this.
听起来就像这样：

298
00:15:12.140 --> 00:15:14.716
We are born into a pitiless universe,
我们生于无情的宇宙，

299
00:15:14.740 --> 00:15:17.916
facing steep odds against life-enabling order
面对着维持生命秩序的巨大挑战，

300
00:15:17.940 --> 00:15:20.340
and in constant jeopardy of falling apart.
并不断陷入分裂的危险之中。

301
00:15:21.180 --> 00:15:24.580
We were shaped by a process that is ruthlessly competitive.
我们成长于残酷的竞争过程。

302
00:15:25.540 --> 00:15:27.316
We are made from crooked timber,
我们是弯木头做的，

303
00:15:27.340 --> 00:15:30.356
vulnerable to illusions, self-centeredness
容易幻想，以自我为中心，

304
00:15:30.380 --> 00:15:32.620
and at times astounding stupidity.
有时愚蠢到令人发指。

305
00:15:33.620 --> 00:15:36.356
Yet human nature has also been blessed with resources
然而，人类本性也被赋予了资源，

306
00:15:36.380 --> 00:15:38.660
that open a space for a kind of redemption.
为一种救赎打开了空间。

307
00:15:39.460 --> 00:15:42.716
We are endowed with the power to combine ideas recursively,
我们被赋予了以递归的方式 组合思想的力量，

308
00:15:42.740 --> 00:15:45.196
to have thoughts about our thoughts.
能够对个人的想法进行自省。

309
00:15:45.220 --> 00:15:47.116
We have an instinct for language,
我们有语言的本能，

310
00:15:47.140 --> 00:15:50.580
allowing us to share the fruits of our ingenuity and experience.
让我们可以分享智慧和经验成果。

311
00:15:51.580 --> 00:15:54.236
We are deepened with the capacity for sympathy,
我们因拥有怜悯、想象、

312
00:15:54.260 --> 00:15:58.380
for pity, imagination, compassion, commiseration.
慈悲、同理心的能力而深化。

313
00:15:59.300 --> 00:16:03.076
These endowments have found ways to magnify their own power.
这些天赐的能力也找到了 扩大其作用的方法。

314
00:16:03.100 --> 00:16:05.116
The scope of language has been augmented
语言的覆盖范围因手写，

315
00:16:05.140 --> 00:16:07.980
by the written, printed and electronic word.
印刷和电子文字而增加。

316
00:16:09.100 --> 00:16:11.116
Our circle of sympathy has been expanded
我们的同情圈

317
00:16:10.336 --> 00:16:14.220
by history, journalism and the narrative arts.
因历史，新闻和叙事艺术而扩大。

318
00:16:14.980 --> 00:16:17.836
And our puny rational faculties have been multiplied
通过理性的规范和制度，

319
00:16:17.860 --> 00:16:20.556
by the norms and institutions of reason,
好奇心，公开辩论，

320
00:16:20.580 --> 00:16:23.876
intellectual curiosity, open debate,
对权威和教条的怀疑，

321
00:16:23.900 --> 00:16:26.596
skepticism of authority and dogma
以及与现实对抗来验证想法的举证责任，

322
00:16:26.620 --> 00:16:28.996
and the burden of proof to verify ideas
我们微小的理性思考能力

323
00:16:29.020 --> 00:16:30.900
by confronting them against reality.
就会成倍增加。

324
00:16:32.140 --> 00:16:34.676
As the spiral of recursive improvement
随着递归改进的螺旋上升的

325
00:16:34.700 --> 00:16:36.316
gathers momentum,
势头不断增强，

326
00:16:36.340 --> 00:16:39.876
we eke out victories against the forces that grind us down,
我们战胜了让我们沮丧的力量，

327
00:16:39.900 --> 00:16:43.156
not least the darker parts of our own nature.
尤其是本性中较黑暗的部分。

328
00:16:43.180 --> 00:16:47.916
We penetrate the mysteries of the cosmos, including life and mind.
我们深入宇宙的奥秘， 包括生命和心灵。

329
00:16:47.940 --> 00:16:51.796
We live longer, suffer less, learn more,
我们活得更久，遭遇更少，学得更多，

330
00:16:51.820 --> 00:16:54.676
get smarter and enjoy more small pleasures
变得更聪明，享受更多的小乐趣

331
00:16:54.700 --> 00:16:56.020
and rich experiences.
以及更丰富的体验。

332
00:16:56.900 --> 00:17:01.516
Fewer of us are killed, assaulted, enslaved, exploited
更少的人被杀害，被袭击， 被奴役，被剥削，

333
00:17:01.540 --> 00:17:03.556
or oppressed by the others.
或被人压迫。

334
00:17:03.580 --> 00:17:08.076
From a few oases, the territories with peace and prosperity are growing
从最初的几块绿洲， 和平与繁荣的领土正在增长，

335
00:17:08.100 --> 00:17:10.460
and could someday encompass the globe.
终有一天，世界将会被其包围。

336
00:17:11.660 --> 00:17:13.556
Much suffering remains
苦难依旧，

337
00:17:13.580 --> 00:17:15.316
and tremendous peril,
危险尚存，

338
00:17:15.340 --> 00:17:18.076
but ideas on how to reduce them have been voiced,
但减少它们的方法已经被提出，

339
00:17:18.100 --> 00:17:21.995
and an infinite number of others are yet to be conceived.
还有无数其他的方法仍在孕育中。

340
00:17:22.020 --> 00:17:24.436
We will never have a perfect world,
我们永远不会拥有完美的世界，

341
00:17:24.460 --> 00:17:26.716
and it would be dangerous to seek one.
寻找完美世界的过程危机重重。

342
00:17:26.740 --> 00:17:29.275
But there's no limit to the betterments we can attain
如果我们继续将知识用于人类福祉，

343
00:17:29.300 --> 00:17:33.179
if we continue to apply knowledge to enhance human flourishing.
就会源源不断的获得更美好的东西。

344
00:17:34.580 --> 00:17:37.716
This heroic story is not just another myth.
这个英雄故事不是另一个神话。

345
00:17:37.740 --> 00:17:40.796
Myths are fictions, but this one is true,
神话是虚构的，但这是真的。

346
00:17:40.820 --> 00:17:44.756
true to the best of our knowledge, which is the only truth we can have.
这是我们所知道的最好的真理， 也是我们唯一能拥有的真理。

347
00:17:44.780 --> 00:17:45.996
As we learn more,
当我们懂得更多，

348
00:17:46.020 --> 00:17:50.476
we can show which parts of the story continue to be true and which ones false,
我们就可以展示故事的哪些部分 继续为真，哪些为假，

349
00:17:50.500 --> 00:17:53.300
as any of them might be and any could become.
而这一结果是随机的。

350
00:17:54.140 --> 00:17:56.676
And this story belongs not to any tribe
这个故事不属于任何一个部落，

351
00:17:56.700 --> 00:17:58.556
but to all of humanity,
而属于全人类，

352
00:17:58.580 --> 00:18:02.276
to any sentient creature with the power of reason
属于任何拥有离职和情感，

353
00:18:02.300 --> 00:18:05.196
and the urge to persist in its being,
以及维系自己生命的欲望的生物。

354
00:18:05.220 --> 00:18:07.156
for it requires only the convictions
因为它只需要相信

355
00:18:07.180 --> 00:18:09.356
that life is better than death,
活着好过死亡，

356
00:18:09.380 --> 00:18:11.316
health is better than sickness,
健康好过疾病，

357
00:18:11.340 --> 00:18:13.476
abundance is better than want,
富足好于渴求，

358
00:18:13.500 --> 00:18:15.916
freedom is better than coercion,
自由好于强迫，

359
00:18:15.940 --> 00:18:18.116
happiness is better than suffering
幸福好于痛苦，

360
00:18:18.140 --> 00:18:21.540
and knowledge is better than ignorance and superstition.
知识胜于无知和迷信。

361
00:18:22.340 --> 00:18:23.556
Thank you.
谢谢。

362
00:18:23.580 --> 00:18:27.380
(Applause)
（鼓掌）